messages.subject: Re: Transcription prices
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 10/5/1999 8:16:50 AM Eastern Daylight Time, Strandbe@aol.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 10/5/1999 8:16:50 AM Eastern Daylight Time,
Strandbe@... writes:

<< have a quick question for anyone out there who is doing transcription work
at home. May I ask what you charge? I suppose it varies in different parts
of the country, but I'm trying to get a feel for hourly or by-the-page
prices. >>

The work I do for the Federal courts is $1.25 per page. However, if you do
corporate work, you could easily charge $3 or $4 a page.

messages.messageBody:
I have a quick question for anyone out there who is doing transcription work
at home. May I ask what you charge? I suppose it varies in different parts
of the country, but I'm trying to get a feel for hourly or by-the-page prices.

Thanks!

Susan
